cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.AR 

This paper discusses lock-free concurrent algorithms and their behavior under certain scheduling conditions. This topic is closely related to distributed computing (cs.DC), operating systems (cs.OS), and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper proposes a new way of analyzing these algorithms, which could be considered programming languages (cs.PL) or architecture (cs.AR) related.
